Flow 2 — after-save (step 16), deliberately recursive

Actions and Related Records (after save), entry condition After_Flow_Stamp__c is null, containing an Update Records element on $Record setting After_Flow_Stamp__c = 'AFTER-SAVE-FLOW'.

That entry condition is what stops it at depth 2 instead of running to the depth-16 exception. Remove it temporarily if you want to watch the ceiling get hit — it's worth doing once

<start>
        <object>Account</object>
        <recordTriggerType>CreateAndUpdate</recordTriggerType>
        <triggerType>RecordAfterSave</triggerType>
        <filterLogic>and</filterLogic>
        <filters>
            <field>After_Flow_Stamp__c</field>
            <operator>IsNull</operator>
            <value><booleanValue>true</booleanValue></value>
        </filters>
        <connector><targetReference>Update_Self</targetReference></connector>
    </start>

