Experiment 2 — trip the validation rule
apex
Account a = new Account(Name = 'Trace Test 2', Rating = 'Hot');  // no Description
try { insert a; } catch (DmlException e) {
    System.debug(LoggingLevel.ERROR, '### CAUGHT: ' + e.getDmlMessage(0));
}
FLOW_START_INTERVIEW_BEGIN|Trace - Before Save          ← ran
CODE_UNIT_STARTED|...BeforeInsert                       ← ran
CODE_UNIT_FINISHED
VALIDATION_RULE|03d...|Trace_Rating_Guard
VALIDATION_FAIL                                          ← stops here
DML_END
USER_DEBUG|### CAUGHT: Hot accounts need a Description.

No AfterInsert. No after-save flow. Everything from step 6 onward is skipped. This is the visual answer to "why didn't my after trigger fire" — and it's also why work you put in a before trigger can be thrown away.

