Reading logs efficiently
bash
sf apex tail log --color                       # live stream while you click in the UI

grep -E 'CODE_UNIT_STARTED|FLOW_START_INTERVIEW_BEGIN|VALIDATION_(RULE|PASS|FAIL)|USER_DEBUG.*###|DML_(BEGIN|END)|WF_' run.log

grep '###' run.log                             # just your trace lines

Marker reference:

Marker	Step	Reads as
CODE_UNIT_STARTED|...trigger event X for [new]	4	before-insert (no Ids yet)
CODE_UNIT_STARTED|...trigger event X for [001...]	8	after-context (Ids present)
FLOW_START_INTERVIEWS_BEGIN above first code unit	3	before-save flow
FLOW_START_INTERVIEWS_BEGIN below after-trigger	16	after-save flow
VALIDATION_RULE / PASS / FAIL	5	custom validation
WF_RULE_EVAL_BEGIN / WF_FIELD_UPDATE	11–12	legacy workflow
DML_BEGIN nested inside DML_BEGIN	—	recursion
FLOW_INTERVIEW_FINISHED with no DML	—	flow ran but changed nothing

